253
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:25,833
C'mon! Cut me a break.

254
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:27,250
[BAYONETTA] My condolences.

255
00:18:27,333 --> 00:18:30,000
But the deal was
I see to the funeral,

256
00:18:30,083 --> 00:18:32,625
and you get me the
information I asked for.

257
00:18:32,708 --> 00:18:34,291
[MAN] Yeah, yeah.

258
00:18:34,375 --> 00:18:37,291
Did anyone ever tell ya
that you're pretty damn bossy

259
00:18:37,375 --> 00:18:40,291
for someone who can't
even remember her own name?

260
00:18:40,375 --> 00:18:43,291
[RODIN] Her name is Bayonetta.

261
00:18:43,375 --> 00:18:46,500
[MAN] That's the name
you gave her, Rodin.

262
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:49,583
Twenty years ago, she
woke up stuck in a casket

263
00:18:49,666 --> 00:18:51,208
at the bottom of a lake.

264
00:18:51,291 --> 00:18:53,041
But she's still one big mystery.

265
00:18:53,125 --> 00:18:56,125
The only thing she remembers
is that she's a witch.

266
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:58,125
I mean killing angels
and offering them up

267
00:18:58,208 --> 00:19:00,208
to demons is great and all...

268
00:19:00,291 --> 00:19:02,125
But as long as she's
working her ass off,

269
00:19:02,208 --> 00:19:03,875
she might as well
make some money.

270
00:19:03,958 --> 00:19:05,458
[BAYONETTA] If I
needed a biographer,

271
00:19:05,541 --> 00:19:07,375
you wouldn't be my first choice.

272
00:19:07,458 --> 00:19:08,875
[cheering on TV]

273
00:19:08,958 --> 00:19:10,208
[REPORTER]
I've just been told...

274
00:19:10,291 --> 00:19:12,125
Mr. Balder of
the Ithavoll Group...

275
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:14,500
is about to appear
for the first time.

276
00:19:14,583 --> 00:19:15,833
It's fair to say...

277
00:19:15,916 --> 00:19:18,375
this mutli-national
conglomerate's vast fortune

278
00:19:18,458 --> 00:19:20,958
supports the economy
here in Vigrid.

279
00:19:21,041 --> 00:19:22,916
Thus, many here are
looking to Mr. Balder

280
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,500
to handle this crisis.

281
00:19:24,583 --> 00:19:25,458
[REPORTER] If he succeeds...

282
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:27,083
[MAN] Hey, that's the guy!

283
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:28,833
I got the scoop
on that big shot,

284
00:19:28,916 --> 00:19:31,083
so I'll give you
the lowdown on him.

285
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:34,625
[MAN] So, he's the head of
all those Ragna believers.

286
00:19:34,708 --> 00:19:36,041
And apparently,
it's the first time

287
00:19:36,125 --> 00:19:38,208
he's shown his face in public.

288
00:19:38,291 --> 00:19:40,041
This just happens
to coincide with the

289
00:19:40,125 --> 00:19:43,833
first resurrection of
Jubileus in five hundred years.

290
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:46,708
Rumor has it, this guy's
been alive since the last one.

291
00:19:46,791 --> 00:19:49,791
And if that's the
truth, he ain't human.

292
00:19:49,875 --> 00:19:52,375
The Ithavoll Group also
has some cutting edge

293
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:55,166
technology that ain't
exactly in keeping with their

294
00:19:55,250 --> 00:19:57,583
"friendly neighborhood
church" image.

295
00:19:57,666 --> 00:20:01,000
But to believers this
tech is a freakin' miracle!

296
00:20:01,083 --> 00:20:04,333
According to my sources,
this Balder guy is a descendent

297
00:20:04,416 --> 00:20:06,708
of the lost sages.
Ones from old stories

298
00:20:06,791 --> 00:20:09,375
that worshipped light
and were enemies of witches.

299
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:11,958
So basically, if my
informants are correct,

300
00:20:12,041 --> 00:20:13,916
this guy is a modern day sage.

301
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:16,500
Let's hope he doesn't try
to burn you at the stake.

302
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:17,875
[chuckles]

303
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:21,625
There's a tasty bit of
info for ya. Not bad, right?

304
00:20:23,125 --> 00:20:24,500
[BAYONETTA gasps]

305
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:32,500
[BALDER] My dear sweet
child... I'm waiting.

306
00:20:35,875 --> 00:20:38,916
[MAN] See Rodin.
She seems happy with that.

307
00:20:41,375 --> 00:20:42,791
[MAN] I'm going home.

308
00:20:42,875 --> 00:20:46,458
My kids are baking me a
birthday cake. Cute fuckers.

309
00:20:46,541 --> 00:20:49,500
Skippin' out without
paying your tab again, Enzo?

310
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:50,916
You can take
care of that.

311
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,791
Call it my birthday
present. Thanks a lot, pal.

312
00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:57,833
[ENZO] I'll give ya a heads
up when I've got another job.

313
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:02,333
Freaky fat-ass
little undertaker man.

314
00:21:02,416 --> 00:21:04,666
[ENZO] Ciao!

315
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:14,500
♪

316
00:21:14,583 --> 00:21:15,750
[RODIN] That's the
thing you were holding

317
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:18,208
when you woke up, right?

318
00:21:18,291 --> 00:21:19,708
Yes.

319
00:21:19,791 --> 00:21:23,250
Do you think it might help
you remember something someday?

320
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:25,250
It might.

321
00:21:25,333 --> 00:21:27,083
But at the moment,
that man Balder of the

322
00:21:27,166 --> 00:21:31,333
Ithavoll Group intrigues me
far more than an old lipstick.

323
00:21:31,416 --> 00:21:33,958
He holds the key to
my missing memories.

324
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:36,333
Of that I feel certain.

325
00:21:36,416 --> 00:21:40,541
You figured that out...
from what Enzo told ya?

326
00:21:43,208 --> 00:21:45,500
Call it a woman's intuition.

327
00:21:45,583 --> 00:21:46,541
Hm.

328
00:21:46,625 --> 00:21:49,166
So Vigrid... that's
your next stop?

329
00:21:49,250 --> 00:21:50,625
[BAYONETTA] Yes.

330
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:01,291
[RODIN] Then I'll hook you up.
Take whatever you want.

331
00:22:09,708 --> 00:22:19,750
♪

332
00:22:19,833 --> 00:22:22,708
[BALDER] I've waited
five hundred years.

333
00:22:22,791 --> 00:22:25,458
Now, the time has come.

334
00:22:25,541 --> 00:22:29,208
She will find her
way here, I have no doubt.

335
00:22:29,291 --> 00:22:32,166
[WOMAN] What then?
Will history repeat itself?

336
00:22:32,250 --> 00:22:34,291
Or have you seen to that?

337
00:22:34,375 --> 00:22:36,625
Her path is predestined.

338
00:22:36,708 --> 00:22:38,750
And I'll tell you how I know.

339
00:22:38,833 --> 00:22:41,291
I understand the
rules of the three worlds;

340
00:22:41,375 --> 00:22:45,916
the Human world, Paradiso,
Inferno. I see it all...

341
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,666
And I have seen our
actions helping the Creator

342
00:22:48,750 --> 00:22:51,583
to start a new
cycle of creation!

343
00:22:51,666 --> 00:22:53,208
[WOMAN] How ironic
that the Right Eye

344
00:22:53,291 --> 00:22:55,500
would choose chaos over order.

345
00:22:55,583 --> 00:22:59,333
[BALDER] You're wrong.
The world is already in chaos.

346
00:22:59,416 --> 00:23:01,041
That is why she
and I must become

347
00:23:01,125 --> 00:23:02,916
the "Eyes of the World."

348
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:05,541
Until the three worlds
form a perfect whole,

349
00:23:05,625 --> 00:23:08,916
there will be no true salvation.

350
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:12,000
Sound's like the
logic of a madman.

351
00:23:12,083 --> 00:23:15,166
You lack the
capacity to understand.

352
00:23:15,250 --> 00:23:18,583
How unfortunate that
you cannot part with me.

353
00:23:18,666 --> 00:23:21,791
[BALDER] I am pleased with
how things are progressing.

354
00:23:21,875 --> 00:23:24,666
The angels have
been working hard.

355
00:23:24,750 --> 00:23:27,250
[BALDER] As have you... Jeanne.

356
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,291
[heavy exhale]

357
00:23:29,375 --> 00:23:32,166
[BALDER] We've waited
five hundred years.

358
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:34,125
Such a long time.

359
00:23:34,208 --> 00:23:37,291
You must be looking forward
to seeing her again.

360
00:23:37,375 --> 00:23:40,083
But do not forget,
everything we do

361
00:23:40,166 --> 00:23:42,708
is to prepare for the coming.

362
00:23:44,791 --> 00:23:50,041
[BALDER] The creation of a
New World is close at hand.

363
00:24:02,625 --> 00:24:05,208
[LUKA] The memory
card's still intact...

364
00:24:06,916 --> 00:24:08,916
But I still didn't
manage to get any pictures

365
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:11,125
of her true form.

366
00:24:12,458 --> 00:24:16,458
You can't hide from me,
Bayonetta. I'll find you.

367
00:24:23,166 --> 00:24:27,333
The Ragna...
descendent of sages...

368
00:24:31,875 --> 00:24:35,708
[LUKA] Wait... Wasn't my father
trying to uncover the truth

369
00:24:35,791 --> 00:24:38,041
about the sages and witches...

370
00:24:38,125 --> 00:24:40,333
when Bayonetta killed him?

371
00:24:46,166 --> 00:24:50,625
[train horn]

372
00:25:03,041 --> 00:25:08,791
[BALDER] Time to wake up,
my dear, sweet child.

373
00:25:13,333 --> 00:25:15,333
[GIRL] Daddy?

374
00:25:15,416 --> 00:25:19,250
That's right. Come dear.

375
00:25:19,333 --> 00:25:20,708
[gasp]

376
00:25:25,750 --> 00:25:28,083
[distant motorcycle engine]

377
00:25:29,250 --> 00:25:39,250
♪

378
00:25:43,916 --> 00:25:45,041
Hm.

379
00:25:45,125 --> 00:25:46,250
Ha!

380
00:25:46,333 --> 00:25:48,458
[screaming]

381
00:26:08,708 --> 00:26:11,291
You must forgive me,
but who are you?

382
00:26:11,375 --> 00:26:12,791
[scoffs]

383
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:17,041
[revs motorcyle engine]

384
00:26:19,041 --> 00:26:30,916
♪

385
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,708
[BAYONETTA] You've
quite the familiar face.

386
00:26:32,791 --> 00:26:35,083
And we seem to be
using the same powers.

387
00:26:35,166 --> 00:26:38,083
So I'll ask again, who are you?

388
00:26:38,166 --> 00:26:40,083
[JEANNE chuckles] Same powers?!

389
00:26:40,166 --> 00:26:43,791
I think your little dip in that
lake has left you a bit rusty.

390
00:26:43,875 --> 00:26:46,500
I have had trouble
remembering things of late...

391
00:26:46,583 --> 00:26:49,708
But have we met? You
seem to know who I am.

392
00:26:49,791 --> 00:26:53,208
It would seem I know who
you are better than you do.

393
00:26:53,291 --> 00:26:55,416
My interest is piqued.

394
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:59,583
I'd be happy to explain
it all if you can defeat me.

395
00:26:59,666 --> 00:27:01,041
Ha!

396
00:27:02,083 --> 00:27:09,125
♪

397
00:27:09,208 --> 00:27:11,333
The fun's just getting started.

398
00:27:11,416 --> 00:27:21,375
♪

399
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:32,875
I remember fighting like this.

400
00:27:32,958 --> 00:27:36,125
Tell me, have I knocked
any of you memories loose?

401
00:27:36,208 --> 00:27:37,875
Nothing so far.

402
00:27:37,958 --> 00:27:39,625
But I have a
feeling I'll remember more

403
00:27:39,708 --> 00:27:42,000
once I've knocked
you unconscious.

404
00:27:42,083 --> 00:27:44,041
You can try.

405
00:27:44,125 --> 00:27:45,500
[JEANNE] Haaaugh!

406
00:27:48,166 --> 00:27:58,125
♪

407
00:28:20,791 --> 00:28:22,208
[gasps]

408
00:28:28,666 --> 00:28:30,583
[JEANNE] You've
really disappointed me.

409
00:28:30,666 --> 00:28:32,541
Is that all you've got?

410
00:28:32,625 --> 00:28:33,916
[BAYONETTA] Oh, I don't know.

411
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:37,041
I think I still have a
few tricks up my sleeve.

412
00:28:37,125 --> 00:28:39,416
[JEANNE chuckles] Is that
right? Then show me what else

413
00:28:39,500 --> 00:28:41,708
you can do with those toys.

414
00:28:41,791 --> 00:28:45,208
I will... since
you're so eager to play.

415
00:28:47,375 --> 00:28:48,416
[BAYONETTA] Uh!

416
00:28:48,500 --> 00:28:49,875
Bloody hell!

417
00:28:50,750 --> 00:28:53,291
What a waste.
You're not ready.

418
00:28:54,541 --> 00:28:56,000
[grunts]

419
00:29:17,666 --> 00:29:27,625
♪

420
00:29:37,750 --> 00:29:41,208
[GIRL] So Daddy,
where's Mummy? Is she here?

421
00:29:41,291 --> 00:29:44,666
[BALDER] Well, that depends.
If you're a good girl,

422
00:29:44,750 --> 00:29:47,458
then Mummy will come
for you very soon.

423
00:29:47,541 --> 00:29:49,666
[GIRL] Cereza's a good girl!

424
00:29:49,750 --> 00:29:52,541
[BALDER] Can you wait
for Mummy all by yourself?

425
00:29:52,625 --> 00:29:54,666
Mhmmm. I can!

426
00:29:58,750 --> 00:30:00,250
[CEREZA shudders]

427
00:30:05,708 --> 00:30:08,416
It's alright
isn't it, Cheshire?

428
00:30:09,666 --> 00:30:12,791
[CEREZA] Hurry Mummy...
Please come quick!

429
00:30:14,541 --> 00:30:17,958
[thunder]

430
00:30:28,125 --> 00:30:30,333
[meow]

431
00:30:30,416 --> 00:30:32,000
Hm...

432
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,875
[BAYONETTA] I don't recall
this bar being here before.

433
00:30:43,958 --> 00:30:46,083
[RODIN] It's a
temporary outpost.

434
00:30:46,166 --> 00:30:50,416
So what'll it be? You here
for business or pleasure?

435
00:30:50,500 --> 00:30:52,166
[BAYONETTA] These
certainly don't live up to

436
00:30:52,250 --> 00:30:54,916
the name "Knight," now did they?

437
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:56,458
[RODIN] These were
real works of art.

438
00:30:56,541 --> 00:30:58,458
What did you do to 'em?

439
00:30:58,541 --> 00:31:00,541
[BAYONETTA] All I did
was have a little shootout

440
00:31:00,625 --> 00:31:03,166
with some awful woman.

441
00:31:03,250 --> 00:31:05,750
You were shooting
at yourself then?

442
00:31:05,833 --> 00:31:07,916
Hm?

443
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:10,166
I'll fix 'em, alright?

444
00:31:10,250 --> 00:31:13,208
[BAYONETTA] Make them a little
tougher this time around.

445
00:31:15,375 --> 00:31:17,666
Can I offer you a drink then?

446
00:31:17,750 --> 00:31:19,458
No, I'm in a hurry.

447
00:31:19,541 --> 00:31:20,916
I hope the next one's better

448
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:24,000
or I may have to put
a chainsaw on my arm.

449
00:31:27,958 --> 00:31:31,166
[engine revs]

450
00:31:41,916 --> 00:31:46,833
[CEREZA] Mummy!
Where are you? Mummy!

451
00:31:58,500 --> 00:32:00,541
[BAYONETTA] Apparently,
Rodin isn't the only one

452
00:32:00,625 --> 00:32:02,708
who wants me to take a detour.

453
00:32:03,916 --> 00:32:06,291
Now then, where exactly am I?

454
00:32:06,375 --> 00:32:09,708
This place is definitely
not a party spot is it?

455
00:32:09,791 --> 00:32:12,958
[CEREZA] Mummy. Mummy!

456
00:32:14,583 --> 00:32:17,541
[crying]

457
00:32:18,750 --> 00:32:22,125
Mummy? Mummy!

458
00:32:23,291 --> 00:32:24,125
Uh...!

459
00:32:24,208 --> 00:32:27,250
[CEREZA] Mummy! Mummy!

460
00:32:29,125 --> 00:32:30,500
[CEREZA] A ghost!

461
00:32:31,375 --> 00:32:33,875
[BAYONETTA] You
can see the angels?

462
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:40,875
[CEREZA shudders]

463
00:32:41,750 --> 00:32:44,791
[CEREZA] Mummy...! Mummy!

464
00:32:44,875 --> 00:32:46,208
Ahhh...

465
00:32:46,291 --> 00:32:48,375
This is inconvenient.

466
00:32:53,333 --> 00:33:00,416
♪

467
00:33:08,583 --> 00:33:10,541
[BAYONETTA] I'm not
usually one to play savior,

468
00:33:10,625 --> 00:33:12,875
but I can make an
exception this once.

469
00:33:12,958 --> 00:33:22,958
♪

470
00:33:31,416 --> 00:33:32,791
[CEREZA screams]

471
00:33:33,875 --> 00:33:36,750
No, Cheshire! Cheshire!

472
00:33:36,833 --> 00:33:38,125
Cheshire?

473
00:33:45,083 --> 00:33:47,041
[screams]

474
00:33:49,666 --> 00:33:51,125
Mummy!

475
00:33:51,208 --> 00:33:53,750
Stop crying now,
understand?

476
00:33:53,833 --> 00:33:55,083
There are
just two things

477
00:33:55,166 --> 00:33:57,083
that I hate
in this world...

478
00:33:57,166 --> 00:34:00,583
And that is cockroaches
and crying babies.

479
00:34:00,666 --> 00:34:03,333
Um, yes... Mummy.

480
00:34:06,750 --> 00:34:08,916
You go take cover, little one.

481
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:12,666
An angel seeks my
attention. I won't be long.

482
00:34:12,750 --> 00:34:14,666
[BAYONETTA] Curious
though... it doesn't seem to

483
00:34:14,750 --> 00:34:16,750
want to hurt this little girl.

484
00:34:17,500 --> 00:34:19,125
[BAYONETTA] Tell me!
What's going on?

485
00:34:19,208 --> 00:34:22,083
Why have you gone through the
trouble of bringing me here?

486
00:34:23,833 --> 00:34:26,000
We'll be safe here, right?

487
00:34:26,083 --> 00:34:29,708
[ARDOR] I must become the
cornerstone of the resurrection!

488
00:34:29,791 --> 00:34:31,708
Ah. Then let's dance!

489
00:34:31,791 --> 00:34:38,666
♪

490
00:34:38,750 --> 00:34:41,333
I'm going to enjoy this.

491
00:34:41,416 --> 00:34:43,125
[power yell]

492
00:34:43,208 --> 00:34:53,166
♪

493
00:34:59,125 --> 00:35:01,375
[CEREZA] Mummy!

494
00:35:10,833 --> 00:35:13,791
You find me
that engaging do you?

495
00:35:13,875 --> 00:35:16,541
[BAYONETTA] And you
intend to take me by force?

496
00:35:17,541 --> 00:35:20,666
[BAYONETTA] Bad boy! That's
no way to treat a girl.

497
00:35:20,750 --> 00:35:23,041
I'll have to
teach you a lesson!

498
00:35:23,125 --> 00:35:33,083
♪

499
00:35:35,541 --> 00:35:38,083
Give it your best
shot! Come on then.

500
00:35:38,166 --> 00:35:40,125
Let's dance, baby!

501
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:45,750
[ARDOR] Glory be to
the Creator, Jubileus!

502
00:35:50,375 --> 00:35:52,625
[BAYONETTA war cry]

503
00:36:08,958 --> 00:36:11,541
[CEREZA] Mummy! Mummy!

504
00:36:11,625 --> 00:36:13,000
Ugh...

505
00:36:14,333 --> 00:36:16,500
[BAYONETTA] What's
your name, little one?

506
00:36:16,583 --> 00:36:20,000
[CEREZA] Cereza...
Did you forget, Mummy?

507
00:36:20,083 --> 00:36:21,750
[BAYONETTA] Probably.
But I likely won't

508
00:36:21,833 --> 00:36:23,833
remember it later, either.

509
00:36:23,916 --> 00:36:26,833
What are you doing in
such a dreadful place?

510
00:36:26,916 --> 00:36:28,708
[CEREZA] My daddy
told me to wait here.

511
00:36:28,791 --> 00:36:31,666
He said if I was good then
Mummy would come and get me.

512
00:36:31,750 --> 00:36:33,750
[BAYONETTA] He
left you all alone?

513
00:36:33,833 --> 00:36:35,583
I'm not all alone, Mummy...

514
00:36:35,666 --> 00:36:37,333
Cheshire's here with me.

515
00:36:37,416 --> 00:36:39,208
[BAYONETTA] You
were crying like a baby.

516
00:36:39,291 --> 00:36:42,166
Please, Mummy...
Let's go home.

517
00:36:42,250 --> 00:36:44,291
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Slow down, little one.

518
00:36:44,375 --> 00:36:48,125
I am not your mother.
So stop calling me that.

519
00:36:48,208 --> 00:36:49,541
I'm sure your
daddy will be ba--

520
00:36:49,625 --> 00:36:51,583
But I want to
stay with you, Mummy.

521
00:36:51,666 --> 00:36:53,041
[giggles]

522
00:36:54,916 --> 00:36:56,666
This is awkward.

523
00:36:56,750 --> 00:36:58,125
Mmm.

524
00:37:02,250 --> 00:37:03,625
[sigh]

525
00:37:05,458 --> 00:37:07,000
[BAYONETTA] Come along.

526
00:37:08,375 --> 00:37:10,875
[CEREZA] Wait, Mummy!

527
00:37:10,958 --> 00:37:12,291
Ow!

528
00:37:15,458 --> 00:37:18,625
You're awfully
clumsy, little one. Hm?

529
00:37:34,541 --> 00:37:37,958
Please... Save his soul...

530
00:37:42,833 --> 00:37:44,500
What is it, Mummy?

531
00:37:44,583 --> 00:37:46,416
[BAYONETTA] Where did
you get this, little one?

532
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:47,916
You gave it
to me, Mummy.

533
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:50,541
For my birthday,
remember?

534
00:37:50,625 --> 00:37:52,083
[giggles]

535
00:37:54,375 --> 00:37:56,458
[BAYONETTA] No more
falling over. Got it?

536
00:37:56,541 --> 00:37:57,791
[CEREZA] Yes!

537
00:38:00,166 --> 00:38:01,875
[BAYONETTA] Make sure
you hold on tight!

538
00:38:01,958 --> 00:38:03,000
[CEREZA] Yes, Mummy!

539
00:38:03,083 --> 00:38:04,958
[BAYONETTA] And no more "Mummy."

540
00:38:05,041 --> 00:38:06,333
[CEREZA] Yes, Mummy!

541
00:38:06,416 --> 00:38:07,625
[BAYONETTA] Uh!

542
00:38:07,708 --> 00:38:09,083
[CEREZA] Ah!

543
00:38:27,750 --> 00:38:32,291
[distant running water]

544
00:38:41,875 --> 00:38:42,750
[giggles]

545
00:38:42,833 --> 00:38:44,666
I miss taking
a bath together!

546
00:38:44,750 --> 00:38:46,416
Isn't this fun, Mummy?

547
00:38:46,500 --> 00:38:48,833
Honestly, little one...
we're only doing this

548
00:38:48,916 --> 00:38:51,416
because you wouldn't
stop nagging me.

549
00:38:58,875 --> 00:39:01,208
[BAYONETTA] Do you with
live your mother, little one?

550
00:39:01,291 --> 00:39:03,875
[CEREZA] You know I don't.
I've lived all by myself

551
00:39:03,958 --> 00:39:06,333
forever and
ever and ever.

552
00:39:06,416 --> 00:39:08,666
Then your mother
hates crybabies too.

553
00:39:08,750 --> 00:39:11,125
But I'm not a crybaby!

554
00:39:11,208 --> 00:39:14,958
Mummy... Why don't
you ever come to visit me?

555
00:39:15,041 --> 00:39:17,250
Why did you leave me on my own?

556
00:39:17,333 --> 00:39:19,250
I don't know why, little one.

557
00:39:19,333 --> 00:39:22,708
And I wouldn't know
because I'm not your mother.

558
00:39:22,791 --> 00:39:24,625
[CEREZA] Mummy's stupid.

559
00:39:24,708 --> 00:39:26,250
[grunts]

560
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:32,083
[BAYONETTA] Were you
really all by yourself?

561
00:39:32,166 --> 00:39:33,708
No friends?

562
00:39:33,791 --> 00:39:35,958
[CEREZA] Just Cheshire.

563
00:39:36,041 --> 00:39:37,500
Mmm.

564
00:39:45,958 --> 00:39:48,625
Ah...!

565
00:39:48,708 --> 00:39:53,083
[CEREZA] Ooh, pretty!
Like it's snowing!

566
00:39:53,166 --> 00:39:55,083
That was easy.

567
00:40:01,791 --> 00:40:05,083
[BAYONETTA] I don't recall
ordering any room service.

568
00:40:05,166 --> 00:40:07,250
[BAYONETTA] You may want
to rethink your methods.

569
00:40:07,333 --> 00:40:09,291
Someone could sue.

570
00:40:09,375 --> 00:40:11,208
There're only so many
methods to choose from

571
00:40:11,291 --> 00:40:13,708
when dealing with a-- whu! Ah!

572
00:40:15,625 --> 00:40:18,166
Mummy, who is
that old man?

573
00:40:18,250 --> 00:40:20,916
[BAYONETTA] That's Cheshire...
I mean, just a pervert who

574
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:23,791
photographs ladies
without their permission.

575
00:40:23,875 --> 00:40:25,375
Pervert?

576
00:40:25,458 --> 00:40:29,208
M-Mummy...? Y-You?!
You have a child? You?!

577
00:40:29,291 --> 00:40:31,750
Of course not. Please.

578
00:40:31,833 --> 00:40:35,833
But... making a baby;
that's another story.

579
00:40:37,583 --> 00:40:39,625
Whoa! Don't
get the wrong idea!

580
00:40:41,333 --> 00:40:45,208
I mean... it might
be... the right idea...

581
00:40:45,291 --> 00:40:47,458
But... just... not right now.

582
00:40:48,625 --> 00:40:49,583
[LUKA screams]

583
00:40:49,666 --> 00:40:52,208
[CEREZA] Ahh! He fell!

584
00:40:52,291 --> 00:40:54,583
Is the old man dead now?

585
00:40:54,666 --> 00:40:56,125
[BAYONETTA] No ghosts
are coming to fetch him,

586
00:40:56,208 --> 00:40:59,458
so he must be alive...
unfortunately.

587
00:41:02,916 --> 00:41:06,125
What gives...?
I'm not an old guy yet.

588
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:37,583
They're asleep, already?

589
00:41:37,666 --> 00:41:39,583
[BAYONETTA] You're
certainly persistent.

590
00:41:39,666 --> 00:41:41,500
How much longer do you
intend to hang around here

591
00:41:41,583 --> 00:41:43,750
with that little
toy of yours, Cheshire?

592
00:41:43,833 --> 00:41:45,583
[LUKA] It's Luka!

593
00:41:51,041 --> 00:41:52,833
[LUKA] Do you understand
what's going on

594
00:41:52,916 --> 00:41:55,916
in this city right
now, Bayonetta?

595
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:57,166
I really don't care.

596
00:41:57,250 --> 00:41:59,500
[LUKA] Why're you here then?

597
00:41:59,583 --> 00:42:01,750
It's got nothing
to do with you.

598
00:42:01,833 --> 00:42:03,000
[LUKA grunts]

599
00:42:03,083 --> 00:42:05,291
Everything you
do has to do with me.

600
00:42:05,375 --> 00:42:07,250
You killed my father.

601
00:42:07,333 --> 00:42:09,750
[BAYONETTA] You know that was
all just a misunderstanding.

602
00:42:09,833 --> 00:42:12,541
[LUKA] You always say that.
Doesn't make it true.

603
00:42:12,625 --> 00:42:14,833
Like me, my father
was a journalist.

604
00:42:14,916 --> 00:42:17,791
He was obsessed with one
case his entire career;

605
00:42:17,875 --> 00:42:20,291
the mystery of
sages and witches.

606
00:42:21,958 --> 00:42:24,958
[LUKA] He probably never dreamed
he'd be killed by a witch.

607
00:42:25,041 --> 00:42:26,708
It's ironic really.

608
00:42:26,791 --> 00:42:28,041
[BAYONETTA] Hm.

609
00:42:28,125 --> 00:42:29,750
[LUKA] I thought that
once I exposed you

610
00:42:29,833 --> 00:42:31,541
for the witch you
are, I might be able

611
00:42:31,625 --> 00:42:34,125
to finally solve the puzzle.

612
00:42:34,208 --> 00:42:36,208
According to my
father's journals...

613
00:42:36,291 --> 00:42:38,416
five hundred years ago...

614
00:42:38,500 --> 00:42:40,416
both witches
and sages alike

615
00:42:40,500 --> 00:42:42,333
just disappeared all at once.

616
00:42:42,416 --> 00:42:45,291
 And their legends
vanished with them.

617
00:42:45,375 --> 00:42:48,291
[LUKA] But then you, Bayonetta,
a witch like those of old,

618
00:42:48,375 --> 00:42:50,666
somehow appeared
twenty years ago.

619
00:42:50,750 --> 00:42:53,666
And now a descendent of
the sages, this Mr. Balder,

620
00:42:53,750 --> 00:42:55,958
has come forward. It
all has something to do

621
00:42:56,041 --> 00:42:58,166
with the resurrection;
I'd bet on it.

622
00:42:58,250 --> 00:43:00,666
You're going to
see Balder, right?

623
00:43:00,750 --> 00:43:02,875
Well... possibly.

624
00:43:02,958 --> 00:43:05,916
[LUKA] When I do, I hope
it helps you remember...

625
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:08,458
what you did that
day twenty years ago...

626
00:43:08,541 --> 00:43:11,666
Why you did it.
Why you killed him!

627
00:43:11,750 --> 00:43:15,000
[CEREZA] Mummy... Mummy...?

628
00:43:15,083 --> 00:43:16,875
Mummy, where did you go?

629
00:43:16,958 --> 00:43:18,625
Little one.

630
00:43:18,708 --> 00:43:20,541
Sorry but I'm babysitting.

631
00:43:20,625 --> 00:43:22,708
Too bad you can't
take over for me.

632
00:43:22,791 --> 00:43:25,291
[BAYONETTA] Say, that
might be a good idea.

633
00:43:25,375 --> 00:43:27,375
[CEREZA] Mummy!

634
00:43:28,875 --> 00:43:32,416
[CEREZA] Mummy. Where
were you? I was lonely.

635
00:43:32,500 --> 00:43:33,833
[BAYONETTA] Stop that.
One more tear

636
00:43:33,916 --> 00:43:35,958
and you'll be
sleeping alone. Got it?

637
00:43:36,041 --> 00:43:40,166
[CEREZA] Yes. You'll never
leave me again, right Mummy?

638
00:43:40,250 --> 00:43:41,625
Heh.

639
00:43:58,583 --> 00:44:06,333
[CEREZA crying]

640
00:44:06,416 --> 00:44:09,000
[sobbing]

641
00:44:09,083 --> 00:44:11,458
What is it? What's
wrong, little girl?

642
00:44:11,541 --> 00:44:14,500
[CEREZA] I'm a... I'm a crybaby.

643
00:44:14,583 --> 00:44:17,166
And Mummy hates crybabies.

644
00:44:17,250 --> 00:44:19,000
So she left me.

645
00:44:19,083 --> 00:44:21,125
So you mean
Bayonetta's gone?

646
00:44:21,208 --> 00:44:22,791
Oh no!

647
00:44:22,875 --> 00:44:26,416
I didn't think she was
serious about me babysitting.

648
00:44:26,500 --> 00:44:28,458
Hey. Don't cry on me, kid.

649
00:44:28,541 --> 00:44:30,375
We'll go look for
your mummy together.

650
00:44:31,333 --> 00:44:32,791
Thanks, old guy.

651
00:44:33,791 --> 00:44:37,500
[LUKA] Listen up. I'm a guy,
but I'm not old. Understand?

652
00:44:37,583 --> 00:44:39,291
[CEREZA] Yes, old man.

653
00:44:39,375 --> 00:44:42,208
[LUKA] Ugh... Why
don't we just get going.

654
00:44:45,125 --> 00:44:47,625
[BALDER] The two eyes
that oversee the world

655
00:44:47,708 --> 00:44:49,958
are about to be reunited.

656
00:44:50,041 --> 00:44:53,916
The resurrection of the
Creator Jubileus is at hand.

657
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:57,500
And all of the
angels are restless.

658
00:44:57,583 --> 00:44:59,708
The followers
of light are agreed.

659
00:44:59,791 --> 00:45:01,458
It has been decided.

660
00:45:01,541 --> 00:45:05,958
She will be sacrificed in
order to awaken the Left Eye.

661
00:45:06,041 --> 00:45:10,875
Light, dark, human. All the
strife, all the struggle...

662
00:45:10,958 --> 00:45:15,958
Everything for the
Creation of a New World!

663
00:45:16,041 --> 00:45:24,708
♪

664
00:45:24,791 --> 00:45:26,125
Hm?

665
00:45:26,208 --> 00:45:36,166
♪

666
00:45:40,500 --> 00:45:42,708
That's a rather
nice set of wheels.

667
00:45:42,791 --> 00:45:45,500
Pity it's going to
end up on the scrap heap.

668
00:45:54,958 --> 00:45:55,750
[GUARD A] Huh?

669
00:45:55,833 --> 00:45:57,333
[GUARD B] What is that?

670
00:45:57,916 --> 00:46:00,208
[GUARD B] I think
something's coming this way.

671
00:46:01,958 --> 00:46:03,125
[GUARD B] Do you see anything?

672
00:46:03,208 --> 00:46:04,375
[GUARD A] No.

673
00:46:04,458 --> 00:46:05,500
[GUARDS] Ah!

674
00:46:05,583 --> 00:46:07,208
Ahhh!

675
00:46:09,250 --> 00:46:19,208
♪

676
00:46:46,500 --> 00:46:48,000
Now I'm cross.

677
00:46:51,750 --> 00:46:53,666
[LUKA] Looks like
we just missed her.

678
00:46:55,875 --> 00:46:57,750
Too bad... But at
least your mummy

679
00:46:57,833 --> 00:46:59,500
made it easy for
us to find her.

680
00:46:59,583 --> 00:47:00,958
Yes!

681
00:47:06,958 --> 00:47:09,125
[BAYONETTA summoning spell]

682
00:47:14,875 --> 00:47:17,166
I've let you
joyride long enough...

683
00:47:17,250 --> 00:47:20,375
Now it's my turn to let
loose and have some fun.

684
00:47:20,458 --> 00:47:30,416
♪

685
00:47:33,958 --> 00:47:35,500
Ooooh...

686
00:47:35,583 --> 00:47:37,500
Next time you
want to pick me up,

687
00:47:37,583 --> 00:47:39,791
have a little
more under the hood.

688
00:47:46,583 --> 00:47:49,166
[bells ringing]

689
00:47:49,250 --> 00:47:51,833
Uh... Another one already?

690
00:47:51,916 --> 00:47:54,416
This is starting
to wear a little thin.

691
00:47:54,500 --> 00:47:57,000
[TEMPERANTIA] May
my eternal soul reside

692
00:47:57,083 --> 00:47:59,833
with the Creator... Jubileus.

693
00:48:00,625 --> 00:48:04,416
[CEREZA] Old man, are we almost
caught up with Mummy yet?

694
00:48:04,500 --> 00:48:07,000
We're nearly there...
Just be patient.

695
00:48:07,083 --> 00:48:08,458
[CEREZA] Yes.

696
00:48:08,541 --> 00:48:10,583
Once we get to the
airport we won't be very far

697
00:48:10,666 --> 00:48:13,250
from the island where
the Ithavoll Tower is.

698
00:48:13,333 --> 00:48:15,416
We'll find her.
Don't worry.

699
00:48:15,500 --> 00:48:17,666
Really? Promise!

700
00:48:17,750 --> 00:48:19,208
Yup.

701
00:48:19,291 --> 00:48:20,750
Unless...

702
00:48:20,833 --> 00:48:22,916
Something really bad's
happened to the airport.

703
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:25,541
Then, we might
have a problem.

704
00:48:25,625 --> 00:48:27,250
Look! We're almost there.

705
00:48:27,333 --> 00:48:28,708
[gasps]

706
00:48:33,708 --> 00:48:36,291
[LUKA] What?! Oh, come on!
You gotta be kidding me!

707
00:48:36,375 --> 00:48:39,708
Now that's just overdoing
it a bit, even for Bayonetta!

708
00:48:39,791 --> 00:48:42,833
[gasps] That ghost... is big!

709
00:48:42,916 --> 00:48:44,333
Mummy!

710
00:48:54,416 --> 00:48:56,291
[BASE GUY] Retreat! Retreat!

711
00:49:08,041 --> 00:49:10,541
[BAYONETTA summoning spell]

712
00:49:17,833 --> 00:49:24,916
[groaning]

713
00:49:25,000 --> 00:49:27,083
[BAYONETTA] The more I hunt...
the better I feel.

714
00:49:27,166 --> 00:49:30,083
It's an amazing rush of power.

715
00:49:30,166 --> 00:49:32,958
And power is such a turn on!

716
00:49:36,875 --> 00:49:39,958
[DEMON grunting]

717
00:49:40,541 --> 00:49:50,500
♪

718
00:49:50,875 --> 00:49:53,041
Your new look suits you!

719
00:49:56,041 --> 00:49:59,416
[TEMPERANTIA moans]

720
00:50:10,916 --> 00:50:13,208
[LUKA] Dammit, Bayonetta! If
I can't find transport around

721
00:50:13,291 --> 00:50:16,125
here we're going to be
in some seriously deep shit!

722
00:50:17,958 --> 00:50:20,583
[LUKA] Don't be afraid!
I just spotted our way out!

723
00:50:20,666 --> 00:50:21,791
Stop it! Wait!

724
00:50:21,875 --> 00:50:22,916
[LUKA] Huh? What is it?

725
00:50:23,000 --> 00:50:24,041
[CEREZA] Put me down.

726
00:50:24,125 --> 00:50:26,125
[LUKA] Be careful,
don't get burned.

727
00:50:27,750 --> 00:50:29,000
Did you see your mummy?

728
00:50:29,083 --> 00:50:31,208
I see ghosts.

729
00:50:31,291 --> 00:50:33,041
Great, she sees ghosts.

730
00:50:33,125 --> 00:50:34,500
They're coming! Look!

731
00:50:34,583 --> 00:50:35,875
 Huh?

732
00:50:35,958 --> 00:50:37,791
[LUKA] Stop kidding
around, little girl.

733
00:50:37,875 --> 00:50:40,000
I don't see anything.

734
00:50:40,083 --> 00:50:42,083
[LUKA sniffing]

735
00:50:42,166 --> 00:50:43,750
Do I smell rosemary?

736
00:50:43,833 --> 00:50:45,666
[CEREZA] Try these, old man.

737
00:50:47,750 --> 00:50:50,541
Ah, that's sweet...
But I told you I'm not old.

738
00:50:50,625 --> 00:50:53,208
My eyesight's just fine,
but it's time to go now.

739
00:50:53,291 --> 00:50:55,375
You have to put them on now!

740
00:50:56,458 --> 00:50:58,083
Alright then.

741
00:51:03,791 --> 00:51:06,791
[LUKA] Holy shit! What
the hell are those things?

742
00:51:06,875 --> 00:51:08,250
Are those angels?

743
00:51:11,625 --> 00:51:14,083
[LUKA] No way! Is
this really happening?

744
00:51:18,625 --> 00:51:20,333
[LUKA] Oh, come on,
these things are angels?!

745
00:51:20,416 --> 00:51:23,000
I thought angels were supposed
to be pretty and play harps!

746
00:51:23,083 --> 00:51:24,458
These guys are monsters!

747
00:51:24,541 --> 00:51:34,500
♪

748
00:51:41,833 --> 00:51:44,500
[BAYONETTA] You actually
chased me here, Cheshire?

749
00:51:49,208 --> 00:51:50,916
You must be mad.

750
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:52,375
Mummy!

751
00:51:53,291 --> 00:51:56,708
[distant crashing]

752
00:52:03,666 --> 00:52:05,458
[LUKA] Shit is that
nightmare an angel, too?

753
00:52:05,541 --> 00:52:07,208
[CEREZA] Uh! Mummy!

754
00:52:07,291 --> 00:52:09,958
She'll be fine! We
have to get outta here!

755
00:52:10,041 --> 00:52:20,000
♪

756
00:52:29,875 --> 00:52:31,833
[LUKA] So, uh, little
girl, does your mummy

757
00:52:31,916 --> 00:52:34,083
fight these big
bad monsters a lot?

758
00:52:34,166 --> 00:52:36,750
[CEREZA] Mummy's a witch
and witches protect people.

759
00:52:36,833 --> 00:52:37,958
They're very strong.

760
00:52:38,041 --> 00:52:40,750
You think that...
witches protect people?

761
00:52:40,833 --> 00:52:43,291
Mhm. Why wouldn't they?

762
00:52:43,375 --> 00:52:45,375
When I grow up
I'll be strong, too.

763
00:52:45,458 --> 00:52:47,166
And then I'll protect Mummy!

764
00:52:47,250 --> 00:52:57,208
♪

765
00:53:00,208 --> 00:53:01,583
[BAYONETTA] Hmph!

766
00:53:11,000 --> 00:53:12,875
Let's see... Perhaps
you'll be prettier

767
00:53:12,958 --> 00:53:14,666
when you're blown to pieces?

768
00:53:14,750 --> 00:53:24,708
♪

769
00:53:35,666 --> 00:53:39,625
[CEREZA] Yay! Mummy did it!
She beat all the ghosts!

770
00:53:39,708 --> 00:53:42,250
[LUKA] Here. You can
have these back now.

771
00:53:42,333 --> 00:53:43,708
Hm...?

772
00:53:44,666 --> 00:53:47,500
Your glasses...
Are they, uh, magic?

773
00:53:47,583 --> 00:53:49,708
[CEREZA] No. They're
not magic, silly.

774
00:53:49,791 --> 00:53:52,166
I can see the
ghosts without them.

775
00:53:59,000 --> 00:54:01,541
[LUKA] Angels? Really...?

776
00:54:01,625 --> 00:54:04,791
And yet somehow I
can still smell her...

777
00:54:04,875 --> 00:54:06,291
[door opens]

778
00:54:09,708 --> 00:54:10,875
[CEREZA] Hm?

779
00:54:10,958 --> 00:54:12,583
Mummy!

780
00:54:15,333 --> 00:54:18,583
Little one... Were you a
crybaby while I was gone?

781
00:54:18,666 --> 00:54:19,958
No, I wasn't!

782
00:54:20,041 --> 00:54:22,041
Good.

783
00:54:22,125 --> 00:54:24,708
When I asked you...
to babysit the little one

784
00:54:24,791 --> 00:54:28,208
I meant at home... Luka.

785
00:54:29,083 --> 00:54:31,208
How many
times have I told you?

786
00:54:31,291 --> 00:54:34,000
[LUKA] I'm not Luka.

787
00:54:34,083 --> 00:54:36,375
I'm Cheshire!
Now stop pissing me off

788
00:54:36,458 --> 00:54:38,708
and get it right already!

789
00:54:39,458 --> 00:54:41,583
[CEREZA] You're
not Cheshire. He is.

790
00:54:41,666 --> 00:54:43,041
Wha--?

791
00:54:49,375 --> 00:54:50,916
Do you think that
you could take us to

792
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:53,916
the Ithavoll Tower, Cheshire...?

793
00:54:54,958 --> 00:54:56,250
[LUKA clearts throat]

794
00:54:56,333 --> 00:54:58,791
Well ladies, you're in luck.
Because that's exactly

795
00:54:58,875 --> 00:55:01,666
where Air Luka
Flight 001 is headed.

796
00:55:01,750 --> 00:55:05,375
Fasten your seatbelts;
this might be a bumpy ride.

797
00:55:08,583 --> 00:55:12,416
[FORTITUDO] The Umbra witch.
She does indeed possess

798
00:55:12,500 --> 00:55:15,291
an outstanding power.

799
00:55:15,375 --> 00:55:18,958
What the sage told us is true.

800
00:55:19,041 --> 00:55:24,875
The two eyes, one of darkness
and the other of light,

801
00:55:24,958 --> 00:55:28,625
have observed this
world for many years.

802
00:55:28,708 --> 00:55:32,625
The creation of a
new world is upon us.

803
00:55:32,708 --> 00:55:38,958
Umbra witch... may the
Creator, Jubileus, grace you.

804
00:55:45,666 --> 00:55:47,125
We've arrived.

805
00:55:50,125 --> 00:55:54,125
[BALDER] It will be good to
see you again, my dear child.

806
00:55:54,208 --> 00:55:57,958
Your difficult
journey is nearing an end.

807
00:55:58,041 --> 00:56:00,208
The key to your
missing memories is ready

808
00:56:00,291 --> 00:56:04,625
[BALDER] and waiting for you,
my dear child. As am I.

809
00:56:04,708 --> 00:56:09,875
Give me everything
you've got. Everything...

810
00:56:10,958 --> 00:56:24,458
[sirens]

811
00:56:30,458 --> 00:56:31,833
Oh shit!

812
00:56:36,708 --> 00:56:38,083
It's on our tail!

813
00:56:43,583 --> 00:56:45,833
[LUKA] What the--?
How are we safe?

814
00:56:46,625 --> 00:56:48,333
Where's Bayonetta?

815
00:56:59,458 --> 00:57:00,833
Hmh.

816
00:57:01,333 --> 00:57:04,958
[JEANNE] You're late...
I've been waiting.

817
00:57:05,041 --> 00:57:06,791
I hope you've got
something a little more

818
00:57:06,875 --> 00:57:09,500
entertaining for me this time.

819
00:57:10,500 --> 00:57:12,541
[BAYONETTA] You'll
find out soon enough.

820
00:57:12,625 --> 00:57:14,666
This time I plan to
pummel you until you

821
00:57:14,750 --> 00:57:19,458
spill your guts...
or tell me everything.

822
00:57:19,541 --> 00:57:24,041
[JEANNE] Go ahead. Beat it
all out of me! If you can.

823
00:57:24,833 --> 00:57:26,583
[grunts]

824
00:57:38,166 --> 00:57:41,333
[JEANNE] Shame that's the only
thing you have to fight with.

825
00:57:54,458 --> 00:57:57,041
[JEANNE] I can still
sense your fear.

826
00:57:57,125 --> 00:57:58,875
[BAYONETTA] Fear?

827
00:57:58,958 --> 00:58:00,583
When your memory returns,

828
00:58:00,666 --> 00:58:02,541
you'll understand everything.

829
00:58:02,625 --> 00:58:06,125
Even so, you'll
still fear your destiny.

830
00:58:07,916 --> 00:58:09,916
[JEANNE] "The intersection
of light and dark

831
00:58:10,000 --> 00:58:12,583
will bring calamity
to this earth."

832
00:58:12,666 --> 00:58:14,208
That was the ancient law.

833
00:58:14,291 --> 00:58:17,291
But it was broken, and the
ensuing disaster sent both

834
00:58:17,375 --> 00:58:19,916
sages and witches
into a spiral of chaos

835
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:21,916
that is still felt to this day.

836
00:58:22,000 --> 00:58:24,041
It was the birth of
a child that set all these

837
00:58:24,125 --> 00:58:28,250
events in motion.
That child was you.

838
00:58:28,333 --> 00:58:30,333
Legend states
that the Creator's power

839
00:58:30,416 --> 00:58:33,500
is known as the
"Eyes of the World."

840
00:58:33,583 --> 00:58:35,583
That power is an awesome one,

841
00:58:35,666 --> 00:58:38,958
and it's half yours.
You are the Left Eye.

842
00:58:44,166 --> 00:58:46,875
[JEANNE] It appears
we have an intruder.

843
00:58:54,708 --> 00:58:56,041
Where am I?

844
00:58:56,125 --> 00:58:59,416
[FORTITUDO] I've been
waiting for you, Left Eye.

845
00:59:00,541 --> 00:59:02,458
[FORTITUDO] Witch Jeanne...

846
00:59:02,541 --> 00:59:04,166
Any action that
hinders the coming

847
00:59:04,250 --> 00:59:07,083
of the Creator
will not be tolerated.

848
00:59:07,166 --> 00:59:09,708
What makes you think an
angel has the authority

849
00:59:09,791 --> 00:59:12,333
to order a witch around?

850
00:59:12,416 --> 00:59:13,791
Get lost.

851
00:59:16,833 --> 00:59:19,125
[FORTITUDO] Insolent witch.

852
00:59:19,208 --> 00:59:21,416
I'll be waiting
for you, Left Eye,

853
00:59:21,500 --> 00:59:24,500
by the side of
my Lord and master.

854
00:59:38,000 --> 00:59:41,458
Nice place, if
you're into purgatory!

855
00:59:41,541 --> 00:59:44,708
Still it's a few
steps up from your bar.

856
00:59:44,791 --> 00:59:45,791
[scoffs]

857
00:59:45,875 --> 00:59:49,208
[distant screeching]

858
00:59:49,291 --> 00:59:52,083
[RODIN] How many times I gotta
tell these morons?

859
00:59:52,166 --> 00:59:54,625
I am not your dance partner!

860
00:59:54,708 --> 00:59:56,916
Aaahhh!

861
00:59:58,041 --> 01:00:00,625
[screeching]

862
01:00:03,541 --> 01:00:05,458
[RODIN] I've got a
new weapon for ya...

863
01:00:05,541 --> 01:00:07,541
The workmanship's solid.

864
01:00:07,625 --> 01:00:09,625
Hm...

865
01:00:09,708 --> 01:00:12,708
Hopefully this new
one will satisfy me.

866
01:00:12,791 --> 01:00:15,125
It won't disappoint.

867
01:00:17,333 --> 01:00:19,750
[power yell]

868
01:00:23,333 --> 01:00:25,416
The Scarborough Fair!

869
01:00:25,500 --> 01:00:28,000
[RODIN] New and improved!
This bad boy might even

870
01:00:28,083 --> 01:00:30,458
be hard for you
to get a handle on.

871
01:00:31,666 --> 01:00:41,625
♪

872
01:00:44,333 --> 01:00:46,416
[RODIN] See you
at the gates of hell.

873
01:00:47,708 --> 01:00:50,291
Perhaps if I feel
like going slumming.

874
01:00:50,375 --> 01:00:51,916
Well that was interesting.

875
01:00:52,000 --> 01:00:54,833
And now it seems we have
a level playing field.

876
01:00:54,916 --> 01:00:57,791
Don't worry...
I'll try to be gentle.

877
01:00:58,666 --> 01:01:01,916
Careful... You really
can't afford to lose...

878
01:01:02,000 --> 01:01:05,416
If you do, that little girl
of yours will disappear.

879
01:01:22,833 --> 01:01:25,291
Yes! Don't hold back!

880
01:01:25,375 --> 01:01:26,875
I remember...

881
01:01:30,666 --> 01:01:34,083
Jeanne, as heir to
the clan, the time has come

882
01:01:34,166 --> 01:01:37,666
to prove your right to
fight under the Umbran name.

883
01:01:37,750 --> 01:01:41,000
You may select
your opponent of choice.

884
01:01:41,083 --> 01:01:44,125
Then I wish to
face the outcast.

885
01:01:44,208 --> 01:01:46,208
No! It is forbidden!

886
01:01:46,291 --> 01:01:48,166
[UMBRAN ELDER] The
child is of impure blood.

887
01:01:48,250 --> 01:01:49,833
Challenging her
would be a violation

888
01:01:49,916 --> 01:01:51,583
of our tenets of faith!

889
01:01:56,125 --> 01:01:58,000
[BAYONETTA] I remember now.

890
01:01:58,083 --> 01:02:00,416
I've been here before.

891
01:02:01,958 --> 01:02:05,291
At last...! We can
finish what we started!

892
01:02:05,625 --> 01:02:11,541
♪

893
01:02:11,625 --> 01:02:15,333
You remember...
So are you still afraid?

894
01:02:31,791 --> 01:02:32,791
[gasp]

895
01:02:32,875 --> 01:02:33,875
Uh!

896
01:02:33,958 --> 01:02:42,875
♪

897
01:02:42,958 --> 01:02:45,458
[JEANNE] Let go of your fear.
Accept your fate.

898
01:02:45,541 --> 01:02:47,916
And feel your power return.

899
01:02:48,000 --> 01:02:49,833
[JEANNE] It is our
charge as witches

900
01:02:49,916 --> 01:02:52,125
to protect the
treasured Left Eye.

901
01:02:52,208 --> 01:02:55,125
Even if it
belongs to an outcast.

902
01:02:56,041 --> 01:02:58,208
You said our charge.

903
01:02:58,291 --> 01:03:08,250
♪

904
01:03:17,375 --> 01:03:19,291
[power yell]

905
01:03:19,375 --> 01:03:21,083
[power yell]

906
01:03:31,041 --> 01:03:32,458
[JEANNE] Ugh...!

907
01:03:32,541 --> 01:03:42,500
♪

908
01:03:49,583 --> 01:03:51,000
[BAYONETTA crying]

909
01:03:51,083 --> 01:03:53,958
Mummy... Mummy!

910
01:03:54,041 --> 01:03:56,250
[shaky breathing]

911
01:03:56,333 --> 01:04:00,375
[crying]

912
01:04:00,458 --> 01:04:02,125
[FORTITUDO chuckles]

913
01:04:02,208 --> 01:04:07,083
The treasured Left Eye of
the witches... is ours now!

914
01:04:08,291 --> 01:04:10,708
[FORTITUDO] Come, Left Eye...

915
01:04:12,333 --> 01:04:16,208
[FORTITUDO] The Creator,
Jubileus, awaits us.

916
01:04:18,416 --> 01:04:21,500
Our treasured
Left Eye, will never...

917
01:04:21,583 --> 01:04:24,583
[JEANNE] fall into the
hands of anyone else!

918
01:04:24,666 --> 01:04:34,666
♪

919
01:04:42,875 --> 01:04:47,583
[BAYONETTA] Jeanne,
it was you... You did it.

920
01:04:56,875 --> 01:04:59,833
[JEANNE] You lost the will to
fight when your mother died.

921
01:04:59,916 --> 01:05:05,458
As a witch I had to protect
you, by any means necessary.

922
01:05:05,541 --> 01:05:07,875
In the innocence
of our childhood,

923
01:05:07,958 --> 01:05:11,583
we used to play
together... as friends.

924
01:05:11,666 --> 01:05:13,583
[BAYONETTA] I remember...

925
01:05:13,666 --> 01:05:16,750
You were my
only friend back then.

926
01:05:16,833 --> 01:05:19,333
So very long ago.

927
01:05:20,875 --> 01:05:24,375
Apart from that stuffed
animal you fancied so.

928
01:05:26,541 --> 01:05:28,541
[BAYONETTA] Jeanne...

929
01:05:28,625 --> 01:05:31,416
When you chose five
hundred years ago...

930
01:05:31,500 --> 01:05:34,125
why did you choose
me as your opponent?

931
01:05:34,208 --> 01:05:37,333
I was the outcast
that everyone hated.

932
01:05:37,416 --> 01:05:40,125
[JEANNE] I wanted to be
the most powerful witch,

933
01:05:40,208 --> 01:05:44,000
and that meant I had to defeat
the most powerful opponent.

934
01:05:44,083 --> 01:05:46,041
That was why.

935
01:05:46,125 --> 01:05:50,583
You cannot run from the
treacherous Lumen sage Balder.

936
01:05:50,666 --> 01:05:53,458
The path you are on
will soon come to an end.

937
01:05:53,541 --> 01:05:56,708
But do not fear
your fate, embrace it!

938
01:05:56,791 --> 01:06:00,166
[JEANNE] Stand...!
Stand and open your eyes!

939
01:06:00,250 --> 01:06:02,541
And remember, for every truth...

940
01:06:02,625 --> 01:06:05,875
there is another...
yet to be seen.

941
01:06:05,958 --> 01:06:07,333
[gasp]

942
01:06:10,666 --> 01:06:12,041
[JEANNE screams]

943
01:06:12,125 --> 01:06:13,500
[BAYONETTA] Jeanne!

944
01:06:16,333 --> 01:06:23,375
[distant rumbling]

945
01:06:24,250 --> 01:06:25,541
Oh, Jeanne.

946
01:06:25,625 --> 01:06:27,958
[door opens]

947
01:06:28,041 --> 01:06:29,750
[CEREZA] Mummy!

948
01:06:30,750 --> 01:06:33,416
Hm... I got us
here in one piece...

949
01:06:33,500 --> 01:06:36,041
But then again it seems
like they were expecting us.

950
01:06:36,125 --> 01:06:37,375
[CEREZA giggles]

951
01:06:37,458 --> 01:06:38,833
Mummy...?

952
01:06:40,250 --> 01:06:44,500
Little one... what treasure
do you love the most?

953
01:06:44,583 --> 01:06:45,916
Cheshire?

954
01:06:46,000 --> 01:06:47,041
[CEREZA] Mnn-mmm.

955
01:06:47,125 --> 01:06:49,250
Cheshire is my friend.

956
01:06:50,416 --> 01:06:52,625
This here is my
greatest treasure.

957
01:06:55,541 --> 01:06:58,541
[BAYONETTA] When you love
something, never lose it.

958
01:06:58,625 --> 01:07:00,750
You must take care
to keep it safe...

959
01:07:00,833 --> 01:07:03,041
and always close to your heart.

960
01:07:03,125 --> 01:07:06,208
[CEREZA] I will! And I made up
my mind not to cry any more.

961
01:07:06,291 --> 01:07:08,166
Because I want to
grow up brave and strong

962
01:07:08,250 --> 01:07:11,541
just like you are Mummy.
You're not afraid of anything!

963
01:07:11,625 --> 01:07:13,916
So I won't be either!

964
01:07:20,333 --> 01:07:22,958
Wait! Are you gonna
confront him all on your own?

965
01:07:23,041 --> 01:07:24,000
[BAYONETTA]
Even if I said "yes"

966
01:07:24,083 --> 01:07:26,125
you'd still tag
along, wouldn't you?

967
01:07:26,208 --> 01:07:28,083
[CEREZA] Wouldn't you?

968
01:07:28,166 --> 01:07:29,750
[chuckles]

969
01:07:30,916 --> 01:07:37,125
[muffled heartbeat]

970
01:07:41,250 --> 01:07:42,541
Ah...!

971
01:07:42,625 --> 01:07:45,041
[LUKA] It does look like
someone's been expecting us.

972
01:07:45,125 --> 01:07:47,416
They even rolled
out the red carpet.

973
01:07:47,500 --> 01:07:51,541
[BALDER] Rise my child.
Realize your true potential!

974
01:07:51,625 --> 01:07:55,166
It's time to open
the "Eyes of the World."

975
01:07:55,250 --> 01:07:57,833
It's Daddy!
My daddy's here!

976
01:07:57,916 --> 01:07:59,625
Wait! Little one!

977
01:07:59,708 --> 01:08:01,083
Her daddy's here?!

978
01:08:01,166 --> 01:08:02,791
[CEREZA] This way!

979
01:08:02,875 --> 01:08:04,250
[BAYONETTA] Little one!

980
01:08:12,500 --> 01:08:15,125
[CEREZA] Look, Daddy!
Now Mummy's here, too.

981
01:08:18,125 --> 01:08:21,375
I have been waiting
a very long time...

982
01:08:21,458 --> 01:08:24,250
for this family reunion.

983
01:08:25,583 --> 01:08:27,083
Save him...

984
01:08:29,083 --> 01:08:32,000
[BALDER] Did you have a good
time visiting with Mummy?

985
01:08:32,083 --> 01:08:35,791
[CEREZA] Uh huh. Mummy's
very strong, and brave too!

986
01:08:35,875 --> 01:08:37,041
[BALDER] I see...

987
01:08:37,125 --> 01:08:38,916
[CEREZA] At first I was
scared of the ghosts,

988
01:08:39,000 --> 01:08:41,875
but Mummy said not to
cry, so I don't anymore.

989
01:08:41,958 --> 01:08:44,500
[BALDER] I think you've
grown up a little, Cereza.

990
01:08:44,583 --> 01:08:46,000
[CEREZA] I have, Daddy!

991
01:08:46,083 --> 01:08:50,083
[BALDER] So... tonight you
sleep alone like a big girl.

992
01:08:50,166 --> 01:08:53,208
[CEREZA] Awww... But I don't
want to go to sleep yet, Daddy.

993
01:08:53,291 --> 01:08:55,625
I still have lots to tell you!

994
01:08:57,083 --> 01:08:58,500
[BALDER] You
can tell me tomorrow.

995
01:08:58,583 --> 01:09:00,208
Right now it's bedtime.

996
01:09:00,291 --> 01:09:01,541
Awe...

997
01:09:01,625 --> 01:09:02,958
Yes, Daddy.

998
01:09:03,041 --> 01:09:05,250
[BALDER] That's a good girl.

999
01:09:07,083 --> 01:09:09,500
[BALDER] Sweet dreams!

1000
01:09:10,750 --> 01:09:12,500
[CEREZA] Good night, Daddy.

1001
01:09:17,708 --> 01:09:19,583
[CEREZA] Mummy...

1002
01:09:19,666 --> 01:09:22,166
I'm not going
to be afraid anymore.

1003
01:09:22,250 --> 01:09:24,333
No matter what.

1004
01:09:25,333 --> 01:09:27,166
That's my girl.

1005
01:09:27,250 --> 01:09:29,333
See you later, Mummy!

1006
01:09:35,125 --> 01:09:38,041
[BAYONETTA] How were you able
to bring me here from the past?

1007
01:09:38,125 --> 01:09:41,208
The past...?
Wha--? Uh.

1008
01:09:41,291 --> 01:09:44,208
[BALDER] I opened a door
of space-time distortion

1009
01:09:44,291 --> 01:09:46,833
through the influence
of Jubileus' coming.

1010
01:09:46,916 --> 01:09:49,833
I wanted you to see both
the light and dark of this

1011
01:09:49,916 --> 01:09:54,458
foolish world through
innocent, untainted eyes.

1012
01:09:54,541 --> 01:09:57,375
He manipulates time?
Who is this guy?

1013
01:09:57,458 --> 01:10:00,625
He is the last survivor
of the Lumen sages...

1014
01:10:00,708 --> 01:10:04,083
This was all
started... by him.

1015
01:10:04,166 --> 01:10:08,666
He is little one's--
No, he is my father.

1016
01:10:08,750 --> 01:10:10,500
[LUKA] Auh...!

1017
01:10:10,583 --> 01:10:14,458
Five hundred years...
since the last time we met.

1018
01:10:14,541 --> 01:10:16,750
[BALDER] And if your
memories were still intact,

1019
01:10:16,833 --> 01:10:20,583
this would have been a
much more emotional reunion.

1020
01:10:20,666 --> 01:10:24,291
Long have I waited to
purge the chaotic worlds.

1021
01:10:24,375 --> 01:10:27,458
Once Jubileus is
resurrected, heaven, hell,

1022
01:10:27,541 --> 01:10:30,708
and this world will
become void and be reborn.

1023
01:10:30,791 --> 01:10:35,083
And in this new world,
you and I will be gods!

1024
01:10:36,833 --> 01:10:38,250
Getting a bit
ahead of ourselves

1025
01:10:38,333 --> 01:10:40,666
aren't we Mr. Ithavoll Big Shot?

1026
01:10:40,750 --> 01:10:42,583
[LUKA] You take this
entrepreneurial philosophy

1027
01:10:42,666 --> 01:10:44,416
a bit seriously, don't ya?

1028
01:10:44,500 --> 01:10:47,541
But it's all diarrhea of
the mouth, if you ask me.

1029
01:10:47,625 --> 01:10:50,750
[BALDER] You must be Luka,
journalist extraordinaire.

1030
01:10:50,833 --> 01:10:53,875
I'm impressed. Like father,
like son, it seems.

1031
01:10:53,958 --> 01:10:56,541
He was also too
smart for his own good

1032
01:10:56,625 --> 01:10:57,833
and didn't know when to quit.

1033
01:10:57,916 --> 01:10:59,583
How do you know
about my father?!

1034
01:10:59,666 --> 01:11:02,291
[BALDER] I used to hire him to
do investigative work for me.

1035
01:11:02,375 --> 01:11:03,333
He was good.

1036
01:11:03,416 --> 01:11:05,333
Everything was
fine until he found

1037
01:11:05,416 --> 01:11:07,750
my long lost Cereza...

1038
01:11:07,833 --> 01:11:11,333
Then it became apparent
he knew a little too much.

1039
01:11:11,416 --> 01:11:13,916
[LUKA] Uh! Hey!
What's happening?!

1040
01:11:15,666 --> 01:11:17,666
I can smell rosemary.

1041
01:11:17,750 --> 01:11:19,458
[LUKA] It was the
exact same smell...

1042
01:11:19,541 --> 01:11:21,250
when my father died.

1043
01:11:30,875 --> 01:11:32,250
[LUKA] Ah...

1044
01:11:33,291 --> 01:11:36,708
[LUKA] At last...
I know the truth.

1045
01:11:36,791 --> 01:11:38,708
You're the one
who killed my father!

1046
01:11:38,791 --> 01:11:40,541
You must have been
very close to him.

1047
01:11:40,625 --> 01:11:43,083
My deepest condolences.

1048
01:11:44,250 --> 01:11:49,000
[LUKA] Bayonetta, I'm sorry
for blaming you all this time.

1049
01:11:49,083 --> 01:11:51,416
[BAYONETTA] It's not like
you mentioned it a lot.

1050
01:11:51,500 --> 01:11:52,875
Heh.

1051
01:11:52,958 --> 01:11:55,750
Well if that little crybaby
could learn to be brave...

1052
01:11:55,833 --> 01:11:58,791
then maybe I could grow
up and be a better man.

1053
01:11:58,875 --> 01:12:01,791
It's time to settle my
accounts and avenge my father

1054
01:12:01,875 --> 01:12:03,375
once and for all!

1055
01:12:04,291 --> 01:12:07,833
You are of no use, however
I am not without dignity.

1056
01:12:07,916 --> 01:12:10,041
[BALDER] I will
allow you to join him.

1057
01:12:13,000 --> 01:12:13,750
Ha!

1058
01:12:13,833 --> 01:12:15,208
Luka!

1059
01:12:17,583 --> 01:12:18,958
[BAYONETTA gasps]

1060
01:12:19,708 --> 01:12:22,000
[BALDER] All roads
lead here, Cereza.

1061
01:12:22,083 --> 01:12:24,750
This is where your journey ends.

1062
01:12:24,833 --> 01:12:26,625
[BAYONETTA]
I don't understand...

1063
01:12:26,708 --> 01:12:28,500
Why bring the
child version of myself

1064
01:12:28,583 --> 01:12:30,458
to this time and place?
And why go through

1065
01:12:30,541 --> 01:12:33,916
such a complicated
charade to lure me here?

1066
01:12:34,750 --> 01:12:38,000
[BALDER] Your battles, your
struggles, seeing the love

1067
01:12:38,083 --> 01:12:40,166
in the eyes of
your younger self.

1068
01:12:40,250 --> 01:12:42,250
Everything you've
experienced has been

1069
01:12:42,333 --> 01:12:44,750
a stepping stone
to your enlightenment.

1070
01:12:44,833 --> 01:12:49,125
All of this was necessary
to awaken the Left Eye.

1071
01:12:49,208 --> 01:12:52,875
You're a nightmare who tried
to throw the world into chaos.

1072
01:12:52,958 --> 01:12:54,166
You killed my mother!

1073
01:12:54,250 --> 01:12:57,125
How dare you speak
of the word "love."

1074
01:12:57,208 --> 01:13:00,291
I am not the one responsible
for Rosa's death...

1075
01:13:00,375 --> 01:13:03,291
The cruel laws of
this world tore us apart.

1076
01:13:03,375 --> 01:13:06,416
Angels impatient for the
resurrection murdered her.

1077
01:13:06,500 --> 01:13:08,583
There was nothing
I could have done.

1078
01:13:08,666 --> 01:13:10,041
But you're a fighter.

1079
01:13:10,125 --> 01:13:12,708
[BALDER] Any angel that
attacked you wound up as fodder

1080
01:13:12,791 --> 01:13:15,750
for your demons, which only
strengthened your powers.

1081
01:13:15,833 --> 01:13:18,250
And then there was Jeanne.

1082
01:13:18,333 --> 01:13:20,791
She was the key to
unlocking the full extent

1083
01:13:20,875 --> 01:13:24,041
of your magic and regaining
the core of yourself.

1084
01:13:24,125 --> 01:13:27,541
In other words, she
gave you back your memory.

1085
01:13:27,625 --> 01:13:31,375
Yes, Jeanne did very well.
She did an excellent job.

1086
01:13:32,583 --> 01:13:33,625
[gun cocks]

1087
01:13:33,708 --> 01:13:35,250
Oh...

1088
01:13:35,333 --> 01:13:37,333
You're insane.

1089
01:13:37,416 --> 01:13:39,000
[BALDER] I beg to differ.

1090
01:13:39,083 --> 01:13:42,250
Oh no, it's not
me who's a madman...

1091
01:13:42,333 --> 01:13:45,125
it's the world
that's gone insane.

1092
01:13:46,875 --> 01:13:49,500
[BALDER] Are you
really going to shoot me?

1093
01:13:51,166 --> 01:13:53,708
[BAYONETTA] Don't
fuck with a witch!

1094
01:13:53,791 --> 01:13:56,333
[BALDER] I don't think
you can pull the trigger.

1095
01:13:56,416 --> 01:13:58,458
I'm your father.

1096
01:14:00,375 --> 01:14:06,416
[BALDER] My lovely,
sweet child... Cereza.

1097
01:14:06,500 --> 01:14:12,041
[muffled heartbeat]

1098
01:14:12,125 --> 01:14:13,500
[gasps]

1099
01:14:14,583 --> 01:14:17,083
The resurrection has begun.

1100
01:14:17,166 --> 01:14:20,500
Let us welcome a new reality!

1101
01:14:20,916 --> 01:14:22,500
[BAYONETTA groans]

1102
01:14:23,875 --> 01:14:27,500
[BAYONETTA groaning]

1103
01:14:30,208 --> 01:14:40,166
♪

1104
01:15:02,750 --> 01:15:06,625
Bringing back a dead god?
You gotta be kidding me.

1105
01:15:06,708 --> 01:15:16,666
♪

1106
01:15:18,333 --> 01:15:20,916
[BALDER] Jubileus...

1107
01:15:21,000 --> 01:15:25,000
Arise now and walk
the earth once more.

1108
01:15:33,208 --> 01:15:37,833
[FORTITUDO] I must become one
with the Creator, Jubileus.

1109
01:15:37,916 --> 01:15:47,916
♪

1110
01:15:58,625 --> 01:16:03,291
[BALDER] After so many years,
the time has finally come.

1111
01:16:03,375 --> 01:16:05,916
We are the "Eyes of the World."

1112
01:16:06,000 --> 01:16:09,416
We will oversee its reformation!

1113
01:16:09,500 --> 01:16:19,458
♪

1114
01:16:24,708 --> 01:16:27,166
[LUKA] Don't tell
me that's Jubileus?!

1115
01:16:27,250 --> 01:16:29,666
Bayonetta!

1116
01:16:37,000 --> 01:16:38,916
[BALDER] It's glorious!

1117
01:16:39,000 --> 01:16:42,208
This is the beginning
of a brand new history

1118
01:16:42,291 --> 01:16:45,458
that we are helping to create!

1119
01:16:48,750 --> 01:16:51,041
[ROSA] Cereza...

1120
01:16:51,125 --> 01:16:53,416
[BAYONETTA] Mummy...?

1121
01:16:53,500 --> 01:16:57,875
Please, Cereza...
you must save him...

1122
01:16:57,958 --> 01:17:01,250
He is imprisoned by
a blinding madness.

1123
01:17:01,333 --> 01:17:03,625
It's destroying him.

1124
01:17:03,708 --> 01:17:06,500
Please, save his soul.

1125
01:17:10,916 --> 01:17:14,000
Yes, Mummy... I will...

1126
01:17:14,916 --> 01:17:17,875
I will do now what
I couldn't do then.

1127
01:17:17,958 --> 01:17:19,166
I'll save him.

1128
01:17:19,250 --> 01:17:25,625
[engine running]

1129
01:17:31,708 --> 01:17:35,541
[BALDER] Oh Jeanne, you
somehow managed to survive.

1130
01:17:35,625 --> 01:17:38,000
[JEANNE] The intersection
of light and darkness...

1131
01:17:38,083 --> 01:17:40,291
will bring calamity to Earth.

1132
01:17:40,375 --> 01:17:43,666
That law... I used
to think it meant her...

1133
01:17:43,750 --> 01:17:46,250
Now... I see it meant you.

1134
01:17:46,333 --> 01:17:47,750
[BALDER] You're too late.

1135
01:17:47,833 --> 01:17:50,458
The creation of a
New World has begun.

1136
01:17:50,541 --> 01:17:52,291
There's no
place in it for you.

1137
01:17:52,375 --> 01:17:54,916
[JEANNE] Oh well.
Maybe next time.

1138
01:18:01,791 --> 01:18:03,541
I'm here for my Umbran sister!

1139
01:18:03,625 --> 01:18:05,375
Fuck your new world!

1140
01:18:06,125 --> 01:18:08,583
[summoning spell]

1141
01:18:16,458 --> 01:18:18,166
Is that you, Jeanne...

1142
01:18:18,250 --> 01:18:20,833
Open your eyes! Wake up!

1143
01:18:20,916 --> 01:18:23,916
[JEANNE] You're stronger than
you were five hundred years ago!

1144
01:18:25,833 --> 01:18:29,625
You can overcome this!
You have to fight!

1145
01:18:29,708 --> 01:18:31,083
Heh.

1146
01:18:37,875 --> 01:18:39,625
[JEANNE chuckles]

1147
01:18:39,708 --> 01:18:43,083
Welcome back. I'll be
keeping an eye on you.

1148
01:18:43,166 --> 01:18:45,458
Oh, you're not dead yet?

1149
01:18:45,541 --> 01:18:46,458
[chuckles]

1150
01:18:46,541 --> 01:18:51,833
[JUBILEUS pained outcry]

1151
01:18:51,916 --> 01:19:02,583
♪

1152
01:19:02,666 --> 01:19:05,000
[BALDER] What have you done?

1153
01:19:05,083 --> 01:19:08,666
Without both Eyes, the
universe will lose its balance

1154
01:19:08,750 --> 01:19:11,833
and face another armageddon!

1155
01:19:19,500 --> 01:19:22,541
[summoning spell]

1156
01:19:25,375 --> 01:19:29,208
[roars]

1157
01:19:36,666 --> 01:19:38,583
[BAYONETTA] Our little
pet's not strong enough!

1158
01:19:38,666 --> 01:19:40,750
It would seem so.

1159
01:19:40,833 --> 01:19:44,458
[BALDER] Cereza,
my own dear child.

1160
01:19:44,541 --> 01:19:47,500
Not only have you
interrupted the resurrection,

1161
01:19:47,583 --> 01:19:51,625
but now you dare to
turn a sword upon me?

1162
01:19:51,708 --> 01:19:55,416
I will destroy you!

1163
01:19:58,541 --> 01:20:00,916
Celestial power at work.

1164
01:20:01,000 --> 01:20:04,291
Cereza... he must
be stopped. Now!

1165
01:20:04,375 --> 01:20:06,750
[BAYONETTA] Obviously.
But in order to do that

1166
01:20:06,833 --> 01:20:08,291
I'll need your help!

1167
01:20:08,375 --> 01:20:09,958
Hmm?

1168
01:20:10,041 --> 01:20:12,208
Something special.

1169
01:20:12,291 --> 01:20:13,666
Heh...

1170
01:20:15,000 --> 01:20:17,041
Sounds good to me, sister!

1171
01:20:17,125 --> 01:20:22,166
[BAYONETTA summoning spell]

1172
01:20:22,250 --> 01:20:29,458
[JEANNE summoning spell]

1173
01:20:38,000 --> 01:20:40,333
[BAYONETTA]
Sheba, Queen of Inferno.

1174
01:20:40,416 --> 01:20:42,958
A fitting match for any god!

1175
01:20:44,791 --> 01:20:46,458
[BAYONETTA] Ready! Here we go!

1176
01:20:46,541 --> 01:20:47,750
[JEANNE] Yes!

1177
01:20:47,833 --> 01:20:51,791
[BALDER power yell]

1178
01:20:54,041 --> 01:20:57,083
[SHEBA outcries]

1179
01:20:59,750 --> 01:21:08,500
[JUBILEUS screaming]

1180
01:21:08,583 --> 01:21:18,583
♪

1181
01:21:38,166 --> 01:21:41,333
[BALDER] This isn't over yet,
Cereza. There's still time!

1182
01:21:41,416 --> 01:21:43,375
We can still
change everything!

1183
01:21:43,458 --> 01:21:46,708
Open your eyes to reality!

1184
01:21:46,791 --> 01:21:50,791
[BAYONETTA] It seems you never
learn, do you Daddy dear?

1185
01:21:50,875 --> 01:21:53,916
Mother was trying
to save your soul.

1186
01:21:55,291 --> 01:21:56,625
[BALDER] Nonsense...

1187
01:21:56,708 --> 01:22:00,291
Only Jubileus and the
Creation of a New World...

1188
01:22:00,375 --> 01:22:02,875
...can bring salvation!

1189
01:22:02,958 --> 01:22:05,375
You're such an egotist.

1190
01:22:05,458 --> 01:22:08,791
What use is a world where you
get your own way all the time?

1191
01:22:08,875 --> 01:22:10,375
It sounds like a bore.

1192
01:22:10,458 --> 01:22:13,583
[BAYONETTA] I think I'll stick
with chaos, if you don't mind.

1193
01:22:15,291 --> 01:22:17,083
[BAYONETTA summoning spell]

1194
01:22:27,083 --> 01:22:29,666
[BALDER] Your
resistance is futile!

1195
01:22:29,750 --> 01:22:31,750
[power yell]

1196
01:22:31,833 --> 01:22:35,458
No, actually,
Father... yours is.

1197
01:22:35,541 --> 01:22:45,541
♪

1198
01:22:49,541 --> 01:22:52,291
[screams]

1199
01:22:52,375 --> 01:22:54,041
All tied up.

1200
01:22:54,125 --> 01:22:56,708
Yes. And nowhere to go.

1201
01:23:08,125 --> 01:23:11,583
You only have one
shot, so make it count.

1202
01:23:20,000 --> 01:23:22,416
Now... you're
about to understand

1203
01:23:22,500 --> 01:23:24,833
[BAYONETTA] exactly
how mother felt.

1204
01:23:27,041 --> 01:23:28,666
[BALDER] My child...

1205
01:23:28,750 --> 01:23:32,875
...this cruel, pathetic
world ripped Rosa and I apart.

1206
01:23:32,958 --> 01:23:35,541
The world must be reborn
in a state of fairness

1207
01:23:35,625 --> 01:23:38,375
and order where such a
thing can never happen!

1208
01:23:38,458 --> 01:23:41,500
Chaos must be eliminated!

1209
01:23:41,583 --> 01:23:44,041
[BAYONETTA] A ludicrous desire.

1210
01:23:44,125 --> 01:23:47,458
Run along. Mummy's waiting.

1211
01:23:49,583 --> 01:23:52,583
[BAYONETTA] Bye... Daddy!

1212
01:24:06,791 --> 01:24:09,833
[ROSA] I will always
love you, my Balder.

1213
01:24:11,750 --> 01:24:13,625
[BALDER] Rosa...

1214
01:24:16,833 --> 01:24:18,291
[BALDER winces]

1215
01:24:18,791 --> 01:24:22,541
And so dies the
last sage. Farewell.

1216
01:24:22,625 --> 01:24:32,166
♪

1217
01:24:32,250 --> 01:24:34,000
[BALDER] Rosa...

1218
01:25:02,250 --> 01:25:06,166
[footsteps]

1219
01:25:11,291 --> 01:25:13,333
Bayonetta...

1220
01:25:20,291 --> 01:25:24,791
♪

1221
01:25:24,875 --> 01:25:26,500
[ENZO] I can't believe
it's been a year

1222
01:25:26,583 --> 01:25:28,666
since Bayonetta disappeared.

1223
01:25:28,750 --> 01:25:30,958
I've got all this
funeral work just piled up

1224
01:25:31,041 --> 01:25:33,750
and she ain't around
to help with any of it.

1225
01:25:35,208 --> 01:25:37,791
[ENZO] I might just have
to find a new racket.

1226
01:25:37,875 --> 01:25:40,458
Hey, Rodin...
So do you think that maybe

1227
01:25:40,541 --> 01:25:42,750
she could be gone for good?

1228
01:25:42,833 --> 01:25:44,666
Who's to say?

1229
01:25:44,750 --> 01:25:46,041
I pour drinks.

1230
01:25:46,125 --> 01:25:48,750
And I make weapons
for killin' angels.

1231
01:25:48,833 --> 01:25:50,541
That's all I do.

1232
01:25:50,625 --> 01:25:53,000
That's a shame...

1233
01:26:03,625 --> 01:26:06,291
[LUKA] Sorry that it
took me so long, Father.

1234
01:26:08,041 --> 01:26:10,750
[LUKA] I did manage to
get it published... but...

1235
01:26:10,833 --> 01:26:13,833
unfortunately it isn't
selling very well.

1236
01:26:17,833 --> 01:26:21,708
Bayonetta, where
did you disappear to?

1237
01:26:24,666 --> 01:26:29,291
[LUKA] But it's okay. I know
we'll meet again. Won't we?

1238
01:26:29,375 --> 01:26:35,333
[bells ringing]

1239
01:26:37,916 --> 01:26:40,250
[BAYONETTA] They're
certainly tenacious.

1240
01:26:40,333 --> 01:26:41,666
I should go home.

1241
01:26:41,750 --> 01:26:43,791
The corpses must be
piling up at the church.

1242
01:26:43,875 --> 01:26:46,625
[JEANNE] It's still hard
to believe you're a nun!

1243
01:26:46,708 --> 01:26:49,833
[BAYONETTA] Honestly,
it's not as bad as you think.

1244
01:26:49,916 --> 01:26:51,625
[BAYONETTA] You should
come try it sometime.

1245
01:26:51,708 --> 01:26:52,750
No thanks.

1246
01:26:52,833 --> 01:26:55,625
I'm perfectly happy
teaching high school.

1247
01:26:55,708 --> 01:26:58,666
Oh, before I go...

